summary: I have been working in engineering as well as commercial departments of many projects during my work experience. After studying advanced business management at PACE, The University of Winnipeg, I updated my knowledge of all aspects of business management and international trading: ready to use this knowledge in my new career, together with help from my past experience. Wonderful experience to study at an international university when you learn greatly about different cultures and nationalities alongside your studies. Talking about past professional experiences: I worked for several oil/gas, petrochemical, and renewable energy international companies in the Netherlands, such as Subsea7 company (a global leader in the delivery of offshore projects and services) as a structural engineer from 2020 to 2021, and Jondishapour company in Iran (a leading Engineering, Procurement, and Construction company). worked in the commercial department of the ABS & Rubber project at the Assaluyeh plant from 2015 to 2019.
